<p>How much turkey do you need to feed family and friends? Plan on about ha=
lf a pound of cooked turkey per guest (Thanksgiving dinner servings only) o=
r 1 pound per guest (Thanksgiving dinner servings plus leftovers). Cooking =
a whole bird reduces the amount of edible meat by 25%, so check out this ch=
art for the size of turkey you need.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-table"><table class=3D"has-fixed-layout"><tbody><=
tr><td><strong>No. of people</strong></td><td><strong>No leftovers</strong>=
</td><td><strong>Includes leftovers</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>3 l=
b. turkey breast</td><td>6-7 lb. turkey breast</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>5=
 lb. turkey breast</td><td>10 lb. whole turkey</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>6=
-7 lb. turkey breast</td><td>13 lb. whole turkey</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td=
>8 lb. turkey breast</td><td>16-17 lb. whole turkey</td></tr><tr><td>6</td>=
<td>10 lb. whole turkey</td><td>20 lb. whole turkey</td></tr><tr><td>7</td>=
<td>11-12 lb. whole turkey</td><td>Two 12 lb. whole turkeys</td></tr><tr><t=
d>8</td><td>13 lb. whole turkey</td><td>Two 14 lb. whole turkeys</td></tr><=
tr><td>9</td><td>15 lb. whole turkey</td><td>Two 15 lb. whole turkeys</td><=
/tr><tr><td>10</td><td>16-17 lb. whole turkey</td><td>Two 17 lb. whole turk=
eys</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>
